node.text: I’m so pleased to be awarded the @prettylittlething LGBTQ+ Supporter of the year award! It’s so important to me to support and be an example for everyone to live there life authentically! You can watch the At Home Awards show on @prettylittlething Instagram LIVE Right now, to see the other amazing winners of the #prettylittlethingawards

node.text: Visited the California / Mexico border to meet with the brave men and woman protecting our border. I will secure the border, finish the wall, and advocate for legal immigration! Can you believe our current governor has never even been here?  Vote him out on September 14!

node.text: As governor I will use state funds to close the gaps in our wall. Fun fact: Gavin Newsom has never even been to the border. Great day meeting with border patrol agents.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner in Venice Beach. May be an image of 4 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Proud to work and meet with the Venice Neighborhood association. They truly are on the front lines of battling the homeless crisis in their community. As governor I will be with you to help the homeless and your community.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner on August 12, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and indoor.

node.text: Great evening with supporters! My favorite part of this campaign is meeting with the voters

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: First stop to highlight homelessness in CA. I am solutions oriented and would reallocate the homeless budget to be based on results - not handouts to special interests!

node.text: As your governor I will show true leadership. Unlike Gavin, I would declare a state of emergency and send state troopers. He wants to look good and I care about solutions. Link in bio to support! Full clip in story’s.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner in San Diego, California. May be an image of 2 people and indoor.

node.text: Always so good to meet with small business owners in California

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner on August 05, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Caitlyn Jenner @Caitlyn_Jenner How successful are recall elections? Only four times in U.S. history has a recall effort against a governor garnered enough signatures to force an election like this one. #RecallGavinNewsom USA TODAY Politics @usatodayDC 1h The list of challengers includes reality star Caitlyn Jenner, radio host Larry Elder and the state's 2018 Republican gubernatorial nominee John Cox. 12:21 PM 8/5/21 Twitter for iPhone 39 11'.

node.text: I get this question every day since I’ve started this campaign to Save California! This is a rare opportunity to remove corrupt power from CA

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner on August 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'How the competition stacks up Campaign contributions come in three flavors: itemized donations, from people who give more than $100, anonymous small dollar contributions from people who gave less than that and unlimited money from self-funded candidates All Donations Self-funded Small dollar Caitlyn Jenner Kevin Paffrath Jenny Rae Le Roux Kevin Kiley Larry Elder $0 $50,000 $100,000 $150,000 $200,000 Source: California Secretary of State Analysis by CalMatters. Only includes committees with reported donations of more than $100,000. Contributions limited to $32,400 per donor per election except for self-funding dollars. CAL MATTERS Flourish chart'.

node.text: Beyond proud of the support we have received from the grassroots! We have the most small dollar donors of all candidates. I’m representing the every day Californian

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Caitlyn Jenner on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'A LOT HAS CHANGED IN THE US SINCE I WON THE GOLD MEDAL AT THE 1976 OLYMPICS, BUT ONE THING SHOULD ALWAYS REMAIN THE SAME- OUR LOVE FOR THIS COUNTRY. I'M A PATRIOT AND |WILL ALWAYS FIGHT FOR CALIFORNIA.'.
